* '''Troubleshooting:''' If Tor Browser problems occur in {{project_name}} such as webpages failing to resolve, then:
** Users are expected to perform the same test on the host ({{non_q_project_name_short}}) or in a non-{{project_name}} VM ({{q_project_name}}); see [[Install_Tor_Browser_Outside_of_{{project_name}}Non-{{project_name}} Tor Browser]]. This step helps to determine whether the problem is related to {{project_name}} or not. 
** It is also sensible to search for the problem on [https://trac.torproject.org/ torproject.org's bug tracker] and report a bug upstream if it has not been notified yet. In that case, when upstream (TPO) fixes the issue, the issue will most likely also get fixed in {{project_name}}.

