= {{project_name}} Tor Browser Differences =
The regular Tor Browser Bundle and {{project_name}} Tor Browser slightly differ. The reason is Tor Browser must be adjusted by {{project_name}} to work behind {{gateway_product_name}}. Despite environmental variable adjustments, the network and browser fingerprint remain the same.

The main {{project_name}} Tor Browser differences can be summarized as follows:

* [[Tor_Browser/Advanced_Users#tor-launcher|tor-launcher]] (Tor connection wizard) will not be shown in {{workstation_product_name}} Tor Browser. Instead, there is [[Anon Connection Wizard]] on {{gateway_product_name}}.
* The Tor Circuit View and Open Network Settings functions have been [[Tor_Browser/Advanced_Users#Disabled_Torbutton_Functions|disabled]] in Torbutton. The former is [[unsupported]] for security reasons, <ref>This is so {{workstation_product_name}} does not have access to the information about which Tor middle relay or Tor entry guard [or bridge] are being used. See also: [[Dev/Control_Port_Filter_Proxy#Indicator_for_current_Circuit_Status_and_Exit_IP]]</ref> while the latter would have no effect since Tor must be configured in the {{gateway_product_name}}.
* The default landing page upon Tor Browser start is set to use a local {{project_name}} resource. <ref>The default Tor Browser Bundle uses <i>about:tor</i> as the landing page. See: https://trac.torproject.org/projects/tor/ticket/13835</ref>
* Prevent [[DoNot#Allow_Tor_over_Tor_Scenarios|Tor over Tor scenario]] in the {{workstation_product_name}}. <ref>
[[Dev/anon-ws-disable-stacked-tor]]
</ref>

{{project_name}} does <i>not</i>:

* Change Tor Browser's [[#Tor_Browser_Internal_Updater|Internal Updater checking mechanism]].
* Modify Tor Browser's startup script, default settings and so on. <ref>In {{workstation_product_name}}, rinetd listens on {{Code2|127.0.0.1}} {{Code2|9150}} and {{Code2|9151}} (Tor Browser's default ports) and forwards them to {{gateway_product_name}} {{Code2|10.152.152.10 9150}} (where a Tor SocksPort is listening) and {{Code2|9151}} (where [[Dev/CPFP|Control Port Filter Proxy]] is listening). Tor does not get started by the {{Code2|[https://gitweb.torproject.org/tor-launcher.git tor-launcher]}} Firefox add-on because the {{Code2|[https://trac.torproject.org/projects/tor/ticket/6009 TOR_SKIP_LAUNCH]}} environment variable has been set set to {{Code2|1}}. See also [[Dev/anon-ws-disable-stacked-tor]].</ref>
